    // Home page news articles
    'home.news.article1.title': 'Community health worker training for health service access organized by STOP AIDS',
    'home.news.article1.excerpt': 'Community health workers have been trained to improve access to health services, as part of a program organized by STOP AIDS with the support of its partners.',
    'home.news.article1.content': 'As part of its ongoing commitment to improving community health, STOP AIDS organized intensive training for community health workers. This initiative aims to strengthen the skills of these essential actors to facilitate access to health services for the most vulnerable populations. The training, which took place over several days, covered various topics such as disease prevention, HIV/AIDS awareness, communication techniques with communities, and referral to appropriate care structures. Participants benefited from practical workshops, role-playing exercises and experience sharing with health professionals. Thanks to financial support from Japan and several donors, this program has enabled community health workers to be equipped with modern educational tools and resources adapted to their field missions. Training beneficiaries expressed their satisfaction and motivation to implement the knowledge acquired to improve care and prevention within their communities. STOP AIDS thus reaffirms its leadership role in promoting community health in Mauritania, by focusing on training, innovation and collaboration with its national and international partners.',
    'home.news.article1.date': 'January 15, 2025',
    'home.news.article1.author': 'STOP AIDS Team',
    
    'home.news.article2.title': 'High-impact activities targeting youth: promotion of FP services and voluntary testing',
    'home.news.article2.excerpt': 'Innovative and participatory activities were conducted with young people to promote family planning and encourage voluntary testing, thus strengthening their access to essential health services.',
    'home.news.article2.content': 'As part of its commitment to youth, STOP AIDS has implemented a series of high-impact activities designed to raise awareness and mobilize young people around family planning (FP) and voluntary testing. Interactive workshops, information sessions and communication campaigns have enabled a wide audience of young people to be reached, promoting exchange, awareness and access to health services. Participants were able to benefit from personalized advice, free testing and support towards care structures. These actions, supported by national and international partners, aim to strengthen youth autonomy, combat misconceptions and promote responsible sexual and reproductive health. The images below illustrate the commitment and active participation of young people during these events.',
    'home.news.article2.date': 'January 10, 2025',
    'home.news.article2.author': 'Dr. Ahmed OULD SALEM',
    
    'home.news.article3.title': 'Impregnation and distribution of mosquito nets in Brakna (PAHABO/BM Project)',
    'home.news.article3.excerpt': 'As part of the World Bank-funded PAHABO project, STOP AIDS conducted a large-scale campaign of impregnation and distribution of impregnated mosquito nets in Brakna, aimed at protecting populations against malaria.',
    'home.news.article3.content': 'As part of the World Bank-funded PAHABO project, STOP AIDS conducted a large-scale campaign of impregnation and distribution of impregnated mosquito nets in Brakna, aimed at protecting populations against malaria. This initiative, which is part of the fight against malaria, has enabled several localities in the Brakna region to be reached. Specialized teams were deployed to raise awareness among populations about the importance of using impregnated mosquito nets and to proceed with their distribution. Beneficiaries received quality mosquito nets, accompanied by usage and maintenance advice. This action helps reduce the incidence of malaria in the region and improve the health of vulnerable populations.',
    'home.news.article3.date': 'January 5, 2025',
    'home.news.article3.author': 'STOP AIDS Team',
    

    
